Meet <b>Amber</b>, our Citizen of the Week!<br><br>Amber lives like a queen at <a href='/home/?user=4evergurls'>26103-B Treetop Road</a> in Ravenwood, and enjoys her neighborhood's charm very much. Since moving to Millsberry on March 1, 2007, she has made great friends and designed an awesome house.<br><br>Amber has always been interested in languages, and currently studies Latin at Millsberry Academy. She finds it fascinating how there are so many ways to communicate, and hopes to become completely fluent in three languages someday. Learning Latin has helped her understand where a lot of English words come from, and she loves the class. Her passion for learning is infectious, and has convinced many other Millsberry Academy students that learning another language is a wonderful thing.<br><br>When not studying hard, Amber practices basketball in the gym. The workout keeps her in shape and in "the zone," and eating healthily keeps her energized. She likes to listen to pop, country, or world music when she's exercising, which makes everything more fun. <br><br>Thanks for being a good citizen, Amber, and congratulations on being named Citizen of the Week!<br><br></div>
